- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Constraint Logic Programming is a popular paradigm in Artificial Intelligence, and the paper proposes an extension to a CLP language, which could be of interest to researchers in this field. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the addition of a new feature to a programming language, which could be relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper deals with formal specification notations such as Z and B, which fall under the scope of formal languages and automata theory.
